@Barry
"...a desk used by George Washington during his time as president."

George Washington was not the President under the Articles of Confederation. In fact, he held no official title after resigning as C-in-C of the Continental Army, until he presided over the Constitutional Convention in 1787...in Philadelphia. I'm not quibbling with you, but most folks assume he was anointed to our highest office as soon as he won the Revolution. Washington actually went home to Mount Vernon for a few years, where he complained about how useless the Confederation was.

